$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Yn wiskunde en kompjûterwittenskip is heksadesimaal (ek basis 16, of hex) in posityf sifersysteem mei in radiks, of basis, fan 16. en A, B, C, D, E, F (of alternatyf a–f) om wearden tsien oant fyftjin foar te stellen. Bygelyks, it heksadesimale getal 2AF3 is gelyk, yn desimaal, oan (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160), of 10.995.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Elk heksadesimale sifer stiet foar fjouwer binêre sifers (bits) (ek wol in &quot;nibble&quot; neamd), en it primêre gebrûk fan heksadesimale notaasje is as in minskefreonlike foarstelling fan binêre kodearre wearden yn kompjûters en digitale elektroanika. Bytewearden kinne bygelyks fariearje fan 0 oant 255 (desimale), mar kinne handiger wurde fertsjintwurdige as twa heksadesimale sifers yn it berik 00 oant FF. Heksadesimale wurdt ek faak brûkt om kompjûterûnthâldadressen foar te stellen.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex is in ôfkoarting fan Hexadecimal, dy&#39;t basearre is op in basis -16-struktuer en wurdt brûkt om te ferienfâldigjen hoe&#39;t ynstruksjes foar kompjûters wurde fertsjintwurdige. Dit nûmersysteem fan 16 symboalen waard ûntwikkele as in middel om in 8-bit binêre getal te remmen, sadat gegevens maklik yn kompjûters kinne wurde kodearre. It kin wurde printe en typt mei twa ferskillende hex sifers mei elk hex sifer toant in nibble of miskien in 4-bits formaat.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Dit nûmer systeem brûkt 16 symboalen dy&#39;t fertsjintwurdige yn in berik fan 0-9 of AF. De 0-9 fertsjintwurdigje nûmers oant njoggen, wylst AF wurdt fertsjintwurdige troch de numerike 10-15. Yn ferliking mei de oare trije soarten nûmersystemen, wurdt it heksadesimale sifersysteem beskôge as de meast effektive.';
